{"id": "duc04-testb-24:9#28", "contents": "The citation from the Karolinska Institute noted that it was a sensation that nitric oxide, a common air pollutant formed when nitrogen burns, could exert important functions in the organism. The research has led to the understanding that nitric oxide acts as a signal molecule in the nervous system, as a weapon against infections, and as a regulator of blood pressure. The prize amount of 7.6 million kronor (approximately $978,000) is divided equally among the three winners."}
